<span id="vi.iv.xxi.xvii-p1"></span> <span id="page_329">p. 329</span>
<span id="vi.iv.xxi.xvii-Page_329"></span><span class="c1"><span
id="vi.iv.xxi.xvii-p1.1"></span>Chapter XVII.—The Way to the Kingdom Not
Concealed from the Israelites.</span>

<span id="vi.iv.xxi.xvii-p2"></span>“But if one shall say nothing was
concealed from the sons of Israel, because it is written, <span
id="fr_1391"></span>[1392](#fn_1391.md) ‘Nothing escaped thy notice, O
Israel (for do not say, O Jacob, The way is hid from me),’ he ought to
understand that the things that belong to the kingdom had been hid from
them, but that the way that leads to the kingdom, that is, the mode of
life, had not been hid from them.  Wherefore it is that He says, ‘For
say not that the way has been hid from me.’  But by the way is meant the
mode of life; for Moses says, <span id="fr_1392"></span>[1393](#fn_1392.md)
‘Behold, I have set before thy face the way of life and the way of
death.’  And the Teacher spoke in harmony with this: <span
id="fr_1393"></span>[1394](#fn_1393.md)   ‘Enter ye through the strait and
narrow way, through which ye shall enter into life.’  And somewhere
else, when one asked Him, <span id="fr_1394"></span>[1395](#fn_1394.md)
‘What shall I do to inherit eternal life?’ He pointed out to him the
commandments of the law.

